[Term]
id: http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000009
name: positive emotional valence
def: "An emotional valence which is inherently pleasant or attractive." [] {IAO:0000119="https://dictionary.apa.org/emotional-valence"}
comment: Emotional valences exist on a continuum from pleasant to unpleasant, or from attractive to aversive.
is_a: http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000035 ! emotional valence
