[Term]
id: http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000016
name: negative emotional valence
def: "An emotional valence which is inherently unpleasant or aversive." [] {IAO:0000119="https://dictionary.apa.org/emotional-valence"}
comment: Emotional valences exist on a continuum from pleasant to unpleasant, or from attractive to aversive.
is_a: http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000035 ! emotional valence
property_value: terms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: terms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0002-7282-0836
property_value: terms:created "2026-03-17T19:27:31Z" xsd:dateTime

[Term]
id: http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000017
name: neutral emotional valence
def: "An emotional valence which is inherently neither pleasant nor unpleasant." [] {IAO:0000119="https://dictionary.apa.org/emotional-valence"}
comment: Emotional valences exist on a continuum from pleasant to unpleasant, or from attractive to aversive. Neutral emotional valences are in the center of this continuum.
is_a: http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000035 ! emotional valence
property_value: terms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: terms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0002-7282-0836
property_value: terms:created "2026-03-17T19:29:48Z" xsd:dateTime

