[Term]
id: http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000035
name: emotional valence
def: "A characteristic of an emotion process reflecting its degree of positivity or negativity." [] {IAO:0000119="https://dictionary.apa.org/emotional-valence"}
comment: According to cognitive appraisal theory, an individual's cognitive appraisal of a stimulus contributes to producing an emotion (with its corresponding emotional valence).
synonym: "hedonic tone" RELATED []
is_a: PATO:0001236
relationship: RO:0000052 http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000000 ! emotion process
relationship: RO:0002353 http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EMRO/0000014 ! cognitive appraisal process
